==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flea-beetle
<hw>Flea"-bee`tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A small beetle of the family <fam>Halticid⟦ae⟧</fam>, of many
species. They have strong posterior legs and leap like fleas. The turnip
flea-beetle (<spn>Phyllotreta vittata</spn>) and that of the grapevine
(<spn>Graptodera chalybea</spn>) are common injurious species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flea-bite</ent>⟦br⟧
